341
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:40,520
That's just too bad, isn't it?

342
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:45,560
- Yes. More this way.
- In here?

343
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:48,240
I'll meet you on board.

344
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:50,440
- I don't wanna see this.
- Alright.

345
00:13:51,640 --> 00:13:52,880
We got a family here.

346
00:13:52,960 --> 00:13:54,040
- How long?
- Please. My God!

347
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:55,600
Come on. Who's on that plane?

348
00:13:55,680 --> 00:13:57,280
You'll all know as soon as I know.

349
00:13:57,360 --> 00:13:58,560
If you need to make a call.

350
00:13:58,640 --> 00:14:01,440
We'll have phones set up
in fifteen minutes.

351
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:22,280
Looks pretty bad.
There's the cockpit.

352
00:14:50,280 --> 00:14:51,960
- John Dantley.
- Jack Colson.

353
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:53,560
- Kim Garfield, Paul Roth.
- Jack Colson.

354
00:14:53,680 --> 00:14:54,960
- Search and Rescue. Listen.
- Hi, it's nice to meet you.

355
00:14:55,040 --> 00:14:56,800
We gotta hike in
a ways to the crash site.

356
00:14:56,880 --> 00:15:00,560
It's just up over that crest,
so follow me and I'll take ya up.

357
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:04,520
Alright, we think the left wing...

358
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:07,160
clipped the top of
these tall trees here.

359
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:12,360
We've got the main impact area here.

360
00:15:25,440 --> 00:15:26,560
Let's go.

361
00:15:32,040 --> 00:15:33,440
Kim, note this.

362
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:35,720
It looks like complete destruction
of the aircraft...

363
00:15:35,800 --> 00:15:39,880
behind the cockpit
