482
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:28,880
No one speaks to the press.
Understood?

483
00:20:29,080 --> 00:20:30,240
Alright.

484
00:20:30,520 --> 00:20:32,720
That's it.
Let's remember why we're all here.

485
00:20:32,800 --> 00:20:35,760
We might actually learn something
from all this. Thank you.

486
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:38,800
I got that D.O.S.T.S.

487
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:42,160
John, about last night, I apologize.

488
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:44,200
But I had to call it
the way I saw it.

489
00:20:44,280 --> 00:20:46,760
I understand.
Do we know where the controller is?

490
00:20:46,840 --> 00:20:48,680
- Right behind you.
- I cannot talk about that.

491
00:20:48,760 --> 00:20:51,200
I can't explain that to you.
I cannot talk to you.

492
00:20:51,280 --> 00:20:53,160
First of all. I'm forty-eight,
right? I'm not forty-six.

493
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:55,000
And second of all, it's
an electrical engineering degree

494
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:57,320
- not a mechanical engineering degree
- I spoke to one of the F.A.A...

495
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:59,560
supes off the record about this guy.

496
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:02,480
Management's been trying to
fire him for the last five years.

497
00:21:02,560 --> 00:21:04,760
- Why?
- Personality conflicts.

498
00:21:04,840 --> 00:21:06,680
He files complaints
compulsively.

499
00:21:06,760 --> 00:21:09,160
- About what?
- Equipment malfunctions...

500
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:12,520
union grievances. According to them,
he looks for problems.

501
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:15,560
This could be
a very short investigation.

502
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:18,040
There's the post-computer,
there's the C.D.C., and there's...

503
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:19,240
- the direct access radar.
- Can we come in and talk to you...

504
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:20,360
- inside your house?
- No, you can't come in...

505
00:21:20,440 --> 00:21:21,800
- my house.
- Contact Frank Wyatt.

506
00:21:21,920 --> 00:21:23,560
He's the facility manager at Midwest.

507
00:21:23,680 --> 00:21:25,200
- I want him to work with us on this.
- No, I'm sorry.

508
00:21:25,280 --> 00:21:27,880
Don't you think the facility manager
might have an agenda here, John?

509
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:29,160
No, not him.

510
00:21:29,240 --> 00:21:30,720
- He's an old friend.
- Frank, good to see you.

511
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:32,960
It's been a long time, John.
I'm honored that you brought me in...

512
00:21:33,040 --> 00:21:34,440
- on the investigation.
- No one else knows...

513
00:21:34,520 --> 00:21:35,920
- the facility better than you do.
- Well...

514
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:37,880
this has sure turned us upside down.

515
00:21:37,960 --> 00:21:40,640
Twenty-two years
and not one black mark.

516
00:21:49,560 --> 00:21:51,560
Just be a minute, Henry.

517
00:21:53,040 --> 00:21:54,720
How many planes were you
in communication with...

518
00:21:54,800 --> 00:21:56,480
at the time of the accident?

519
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:58,760
- Ten.
- And how long...

520
00:21:58,840 --> 00:22:00,360
had you been on your scope?

521
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:03,480
About two hours and
thirty-five minutes.

522
00:22:09,160 --> 00:22:11,320
I wish I could hear what the hell
he was sayin' in there.

523
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:14,480
He's sayin' I worked him
overtime yesterday.

524
00:22:14,560 --> 00:22:15,760
Him and ten other guys.

525
00:22:15,840 --> 00:22:18,240
Drake is not ten other guys.

526
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:20,240
- He's gonna blame me.
- And I handed him off...

527
00:22:20,320 --> 00:22:22,680
too many planes.
He could say anything he wants to.

528
00:22:22,760 --> 00:22:24,960
The truth is, he screwed up, right?

529
00:22:25,040 --> 00:22:27,320
- Yes, he did.
- Guys, we don't know that.

530
00:22:27,400 --> 00:22:29,480
Karen, I saw that cargo jet
on my screen...

531
00:22:29,560 --> 00:22:32,840
and I saw it on his screen, okay?
You saw it, right?

532
00:22:33,200 --> 00:22:34,240
I don't know, man.

533
00:22:34,360 --> 00:22:37,520
Don't say you don't know.
We gotta get the story straight.

534
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:41,080
- I'm just a trainee.
- No. You're there.

535
00:22:42,120 --> 00:22:44,480
- I think I should go to the shrink.
- Shrink?

536
00:22:44,560 --> 00:22:46,840
This has got nothin' to do
with a shrink.

537
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:48,440
This is about what you saw.

538
00:22:48,520 --> 00:22:50,840
Now, what I saw were two planes
on a collision course...

539
00:22:50,920 --> 00:22:53,760
that Drake did not separate in time.

540
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:58,680
When did you
first encounter the P.D.O.'s?

541
00:22:58,760 --> 00:23:01,320
P.D.O. was westbound
at 21,000 feet...

542
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:03,480
and requested permission
to climb to 28,000.

543
00:23:03,560 --> 00:23:06,520
Didn't you see tine P.D.O.
climbing into Global at 26,000 feet?

544
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:09,320
When I climbed P.D.O.,
Global was not a factor.

545
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:11,320
I had sufficient separation.

546
00:23:11,400 --> 00:23:13,520
Obviously, I didn't see P.D.O.
climb into Global.

547
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:15,160
- Why not?
- P.D.O. data block...

548
00:23:15,240 --> 00:23:16,600
disappeared from my screen.

549
00:23:16,680 --> 00:23:18,040
- Why did you take...
- Excuse me.

550
00:23:18,120 --> 00:23:20,040
What do you mean it disappeared?

551
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:23,320
Before the collision, I had a glitch.

552
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:25,040
A blackout on my screen.

553
00:23:25,120 --> 00:23:28,320
After the blackout,
the data block vanished.

554
00:23:28,400 --> 00:23:31,720
So you're telling us you never
even saw the P.D.O. at 26,000 feet.

555
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:34,280
The data block came back on
my screen just before the collision.

556
00:23:34,360 --> 00:23:36,560
How long was your screen blacked out?

557
00:23:37,280 --> 00:23:39,120
Two, maybe three seconds.

558
00:23:39,200 --> 00:23:41,760
And did the outage occur
in the entire facility?

559
00:23:42,600 --> 00:23:44,480
I've no way of knowing that.

560
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:48,520
According to the preliminary report,
there was no blackout reported.

561
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:50,080
Did the supervisor see it?

562
00:23:50,160 --> 00:23:53,120
- I haven't spoken to the supervisor.
- Did you alert your supervisor?

563
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:54,560
I requested an unsatisfactory...

564
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:56,440
- condition report.
- But to your knowledge...

565
00:23:56,520 --> 00:23:58,280
he didn't see it happen?

566
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:01,000
Did anyone see it?

567
00:24:01,080 --> 00:24:03,800
I'm telling you,
I had a blackout on my screen!

568
00:24:03,880 --> 00:24:06,240
I tried to establish radio contact
with the P.D.O.

569
00:24:06,320 --> 00:24:07,800
but I didn't see it!
You didn't see it...

570
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:09,440
- or it wasn't there?
- It wasn't there.

571
00:24:09,520 --> 00:24:11,000
Alright, let's go back
to the instructions...

572
00:24:11,080 --> 00:24:13,720
- that you gave 1025. If I may?
- Please.

573
00:24:13,800 --> 00:24:16,200
T-CAS, the pilot's on-board
warning device...

574
00:24:16,280 --> 00:24:20,200
indicated conflicting traffic to 1025
and instructed the pilot to descend.

575
00:24:20,280 --> 00:24:22,720
But you denied his request and
told him to maintain altitude.

576
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:24,160
- It's correct?
- I had other traffic.

577
00:24:24,240 --> 00:24:25,760
I didn't know where
the P.D.O. jet was.

578
00:24:25,840 --> 00:24:30,200
Why would you climb P.D.O from
21 to 28 when you had a 757 at 26?

579
00:24:30,280 --> 00:24:33,480
I've warned this facility about
the sub-standard equipment we have.

580
00:24:33,560 --> 00:24:36,280
I've warned this facility
about deficiencies in the system.

581
00:24:36,360 --> 00:24:38,480
Radar blackouts,
communication outages.

582
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:41,280
I've telephoned
the F.A.A. Administrator's hotline.

583
00:24:41,360 --> 00:24:43,360
I filed two unsatisfactory
condition reports...

584
00:24:43,440 --> 00:24:45,240
in the last two months
on the very same scope...

585
00:24:45,360 --> 00:24:47,160
- I was using!
- Answer his question, Henry.

586
00:24:47,280 --> 00:24:50,360
Why'd ya climb P.D.O.
from 21,000 feet to 28,000 feet...

587
00:24:50,440 --> 00:24:52,280
when you had a 757 at 26?

588
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:56,360
I told you the Global's not a factor.
I could see both of those planes.

589
00:24:56,440 --> 00:24:59,680
So you became confused when P.D.O.
as you allege, disappeared.

590
00:24:59,760 --> 00:25:02,320
No. Yes! Fie, yeah, I was confused!

591
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:05,320
No, see what do you mean "allege?"
you're putting words in my mouth now.

592
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:07,000
I don't allege anything.
The system...

593
00:25:07,080 --> 00:25:08,240
- is unsafe. It's in jeopardy!
- According to the data we've...

594
00:25:08,320 --> 00:25:10,320
Henry, according to the data we've...

595
00:25:10,400 --> 00:25:12,640
you say one thing,
the radar printout says another.

596
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:16,200
You're confused and you contradieted
the computer's instructions.

597
00:25:16,280 --> 00:25:17,840
Let's talk about that for a minute.

598
00:25:17,920 --> 00:25:20,880
It's accepted practice that if
it's your word against the computer

599
00:25:20,960 --> 00:25:22,480
the computer has precedence.

600
00:25:22,600 --> 00:25:24,520
That's ludicrous! How can you
give the computer precedence...

601
00:25:24,640 --> 00:25:26,680
when you can't even believe
what it's saying?

602
00:25:26,760 --> 00:25:27,920
Ask the pilots.

603
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:31,200
Even the T-CAS system
makes mistakes sometimes.

604
00:25:31,280 --> 00:25:33,160
I warned you. Mr. Wyatt.
I warned you!

605
00:25:33,240 --> 00:25:35,040
We've to trust the technology.

606
00:25:35,120 --> 00:25:36,880
You gave the pilot improper
instructions.

607
00:25:36,960 --> 00:25:38,520
- Is that true or not true?
- You're warned that...

608
00:25:38,600 --> 00:25:40,160
- this was gonna happen.
- Is it true or not true?

609
00:25:40,240 --> 00:25:42,560
- You're warned!
- Did you give the pilot...

610
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:44,480
improper instructions?

611
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:56,640
This is the scope that Drake used.

612
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:59,560
He's finishing up
a diagnostic check on it right now.

613
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:01,840
Test panel looks okay.
Character generator functions.

614
00:26:01,920 --> 00:26:03,640
Character gen...
How old is this scope?

615
00:26:03,720 --> 00:26:05,600
- Older than you.
- We're in transition.

616
00:26:05,680 --> 00:26:07,720
We're due for new equipment
in two years.

617
00:26:07,840 --> 00:26:09,720
- So they say.
- I've hooked into a sector...

618
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:13,120
for the last five hours. This is
the same traffic Drake had yesterday.

619
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:15,160
It seems to be functioning fine.

620
00:26:15,240 --> 00:26:16,680
How long do you want me
to stay on it?

621
00:26:16,760 --> 00:26:18,120
Five hours isn't long enough.

622
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:20,360
Hook up a video monitor to it
and record it.

623
00:26:20,440 --> 00:26:23,000
Drake says he reported two
unsatisfactory condition reports...

624
00:26:23,080 --> 00:26:25,520
on this scope. I wanna see 'em.
All the maintenance records, too.

625
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:27,160
Did anybody
touch this scope last night?

626
00:26:27,240 --> 00:26:29,720
I run the department.
Nobody touched it.

627
00:26:29,840 --> 00:26:31,480
Let me know what happens.

628
00:26:32,520 --> 00:26:34,400
- What's Henry Drake's status here?
- I'm sure...

629
00:26:34,480 --> 00:26:36,880
he'd like to have his job back,
but he's not gonna get it though.

630
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:38,440
I gotta find something else
for him to do.

631
00:26:38,520 --> 00:26:40,280
- Union rules.
- That glitch he talked about...

632
00:26:40,400 --> 00:26:42,440
the data disappearing from the screen
that ever happen to you before?

633
00:26:42,520 --> 00:26:44,520
Not to my knowledge. I'll go through
the reports and check.

634
00:26:44,600 --> 00:26:46,160
- Did you see the radar data?
- Yeah, but that doesn't...

635
00:26:46,240 --> 00:26:49,040
prove him wrong. Missing data's
not gonna show up on a radar report.

636
00:26:49,120 --> 00:26:52,000
We need the black box to show if
there's a problem with the avionics.

637
00:26:52,080 --> 00:26:53,880
- How long has Drake worked here?
- Twenty years.

638
00:26:53,960 --> 00:26:55,800
Most of my controllers
burn out after ten...

639
00:26:55,880 --> 00:26:59,600
and move upstairs into management,
but Henry, well, ya know.

640
00:26:59,680 --> 00:27:03,040
Henry Drake's not exactly
what ya call management material.

641
00:27:03,120 --> 00:27:05,880
This equipment is what,
1960s' military?

642
00:27:05,960 --> 00:27:07,680
1950s.

643
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:10,320
My dad says you guys had more
sophisticated equipment back...

644
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:11,480
when you're in the Navy.

645
00:27:11,560 --> 00:27:13,360
There's nothing wrong
with the technology, John.

646
00:27:13,440 --> 00:27:14,800
We may have a few more airplanes
in the sky...

647
00:27:14,920 --> 00:27:17,640
but that's not the system's fault.
It works.

648
00:27:17,720 --> 00:27:20,080
Yeah, Barbara, is he there?

649
00:27:21,240 --> 00:27:23,200
Yeah, sure. I'll hold.

650
00:27:23,760 --> 00:27:26,280
Hey, what'd you find out?

651
00:27:26,360 --> 00:27:27,920
Drake's scope checked out.

652
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:29,120
Really?

653
00:27:29,200 --> 00:27:31,560
- What about those reports he filed?
- They weren't there.

654
00:27:31,640 --> 00:27:33,040
- What do mean they weren't there?
- They weren't there.

655
00:27:33,120 --> 00:27:37,480
The F.A.A. has no record of any
unsatisfactory reports being filed...

656
00:27:37,560 --> 00:27:39,920
or any service on the scope
in the last two months.

657
00:27:40,000 --> 00:27:41,040
That's weird.

658
00:27:41,120 --> 00:27:43,800
- Did we check the D.C. office?
- It's not there.

659
00:27:43,880 --> 00:27:45,520
But I did find out
something interesting.

660
00:27:45,600 --> 00:27:46,720
What?

661
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:51,360
There're five power outages
in the facility.

662
00:27:51,440 --> 00:27:53,840
Blackouts? Caused by?

663
00:27:53,920 --> 00:27:57,080
Software glitch, power interruption,
stuck computer key...

664
00:27:57,160 --> 00:27:59,280
that one knocked him out
for fifteen minutes.

665
00:27:59,360 --> 00:28:01,520
What's falling out of
that helicopter?

666
00:28:01,600 --> 00:28:02,880
Flowers.

667
00:28:03,400 --> 00:28:05,920
From the families of the victims.

668
00:28:06,040 --> 00:28:08,080
That's as close as they could get.

669
00:28:10,520 --> 00:28:12,440
I saw Catherine a couple months ago.

670
00:28:12,520 --> 00:28:14,920
- I thought you guys broke up.
- Yeah, we did.

671
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:17,480
But I was in Atlanta,
so I called her.

672
00:28:17,560 --> 00:28:20,720
We got together a couple times.
It's great.

673
00:28:21,520 --> 00:28:24,040
I don't know why, maybe 'cause
there was no pressure on us...

674
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:26,920
or something,
but it was really, really nice.

675
00:28:27,640 --> 00:28:30,600
I called her a couple of times
when I got back to D.C., but...

676
00:28:31,200 --> 00:28:33,080
she never called me back.

677
00:28:34,600 --> 00:28:36,080
Mr. Dantley.

678
00:28:40,320 --> 00:28:42,280
Park that loader right here.

679
00:28:43,480 --> 00:28:46,800
- How many are there right now?
- All done.

680
00:28:49,320 --> 00:28:51,360
- Bring it down.
- Let's go.

681
00:28:52,440 --> 00:28:54,560
- How's that?
- That's good.

682
00:29:00,320 --> 00:29:02,600
- Mr. Dantley.
- I'm not supposed to talk to you.

683
00:29:02,680 --> 00:29:05,040
- I just want to talk.
- You want this incident reported?

684
00:29:05,160 --> 00:29:06,840
It's not gonna help you out.

685
00:29:06,920 --> 00:29:08,760
Why won't anybody listen to me?

686
00:29:08,840 --> 00:29:10,840
I'm not crazy, I know what I saw.

687
00:29:10,920 --> 00:29:13,440
That plane was not on my scope.

688
00:29:13,520 --> 00:29:15,240
Did you find the unsatisfactory
condition reports...

689
00:29:15,320 --> 00:29:16,800
- I filed?
- They weren't there.

690
00:29:16,920 --> 00:29:19,680
- How? I filed those reports.
- They weren't there.

691
00:29:20,840 --> 00:29:22,680
- They buried them.
- Who?

692
00:29:22,760 --> 00:29:24,040
They'll bury reports.
They'll do whatever...

693
00:29:24,120 --> 00:29:25,200
- they want!
- Tell me something. How come...

694
00:29:25,280 --> 00:29:27,320
out of thirty-five unsatisfactory
condition reports...

695
00:29:27,400 --> 00:29:30,360
filed in the last couple years,
you filed thirty-two of 'em?

696
00:29:30,520 --> 00:29:31,680
Because I speak up.

697
00:29:31,760 --> 00:29:33,360
Just because you speak up
doesn't mean anyone's gonna...

698
00:29:33,440 --> 00:29:35,280
- believe you
- Listen.

699
00:29:35,360 --> 00:29:39,240
Could I look you in the eye like this
if I killed all those people?

700
00:29:41,280 --> 00:29:43,120
Good night. Mr. Drake.

701
00:29:48,160 --> 00:29:49,400
A little higher.

702
00:29:49,480 --> 00:29:51,560
- John!
- Yeah.

703
00:29:51,640 --> 00:29:55,120
- We found the black box.
- They got it.

704
00:29:56,520 --> 00:29:57,880
- Traffic.
- Now you can see the P.D.O...

705
00:29:57,960 --> 00:29:59,040
- Traffic.
- approaching in the computer...

706
00:29:59,120 --> 00:30:00,120
- recreation.
- Traffic.

707
00:30:00,200 --> 00:30:01,480
What the hell are they waiting for?

708
00:30:01,560 --> 00:30:03,920
Traffic, descend now. Traffic...

709
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:05,720
The crew is getting impatient.

710
00:30:05,800 --> 00:30:08,240
The controller's telling
the Global pilot to maintain...

711
00:30:08,320 --> 00:30:09,800
T-CAS is telling him to descend.

712
00:30:09,880 --> 00:30:12,200
The Global pilot's
receiving conflicting commands.

713
00:30:12,280 --> 00:30:13,760
- Center, we've traffic somewhere.
- Traffic, descend now.

714
00:30:13,840 --> 00:30:16,320
- T-CAS is telling us to descend.
- Traffic, descend now. Traffic.

715
00:30:16,400 --> 00:30:18,080
- Negative, 1025, do not descend.
- Traffic.

716
00:30:18,160 --> 00:30:20,480
- Maintain flight level 260.
- Traffic, decend...

717
00:30:20,560 --> 00:30:22,800
Again the controller gives him
the wrong command.

