01:04:19,080 --> 01:04:22,560
I'm not saying it's your fault.
Why are you taking it so personally?

1436
01:04:23,440 --> 01:04:27,240
Yeah? Who is it? Yeah, hang on.

1437
01:04:27,320 --> 01:04:29,640
Karen, it's for you. It's "some guy."

1438
01:04:29,720 --> 01:04:31,760
He's goin' after that pension,
baby, you know it!

1439
01:04:31,840 --> 01:04:33,680
- You guys give me a headache.
- Careful.

1440
01:04:33,800 --> 01:04:36,720
- Hello?
- Karen, it's me, Henry.

1441
01:04:36,840 --> 01:04:38,360
- Where are you?
- I'm just gonna ask you...

1442
01:04:38,440 --> 01:04:40,320
to do one thing, okay?

1443
01:04:40,440 --> 01:04:43,680
Karen? Would you just do
this one thing for me?

1444
01:04:43,760 --> 01:04:46,520
Do not go to work at the facility
on Wednesday.

1445
01:04:46,600 --> 01:04:48,520
- And don't fly.
- What are you saying?

1446
01:04:48,600 --> 01:04:49,960
Just do what I'm telling you to do.

1447
01:04:50,040 --> 01:04:52,160
Do not fly or go to work
at the facility on Wednesday.

1448
01:04:52,240 --> 01:04:54,240
Listen, they wanna help you.

1449
01:05:07,120 --> 01:05:08,600
Tag that and get a copy to Paul Roth.

1450
01:05:08,680 --> 01:05:10,720
- As soon as ya can. Thanks.
- Will do.

1451
01:05:22,120 --> 01:05:23,320
I think Henry's gonna do something.

1452
01:05:23,400 --> 01:05:24,440
- What?
- I don't know what.

1453
01:05:24,520 --> 01:05:25,760
But he called me and
told me not to go...

1454
01:05:25,840 --> 01:05:27,680
near the facility or
fly on Wednesday.

1455
01:05:27,760 --> 01:05:30,880
This Wednesday? Two days from now.
Did he say why?

1456
01:05:30,960 --> 01:05:32,160
No.

1457
01:05:32,240 --> 01:05:35,200
That's the day before Thanksgiving.
Excuse me.

1458
01:05:35,400 --> 01:05:37,080
He told her not to fly
or go to the facility.

1459
01:05:37,160 --> 01:05:38,880
Now, I'd take that
as a serious threat.

1460
01:05:38,960 --> 01:05:40,600
You don't know Henry Drake like I do.
He's all talk.

1461
01:05:40,680 --> 01:05:42,320
You're the one that accused him
of shutting down the system.

1462
01:05:42,400 --> 01:05:45,320
He doesn't work here anymore. As long
as he's out there and not in here...

1463
01:05:45,400 --> 01:05:46,560
- he's not a threat.
- Is there any way that he could...

1464
01:05:46,640 --> 01:05:48,200
- get in here?
- How? The facility's...

1465
01:05:48,280 --> 01:05:49,360
guarded twenty-four hours a day.

1466
01:05:49,440 --> 01:05:51,640
We've changed the security codes.
How can he get in?

1467
01:05:51,720 --> 01:05:54,960
We're meeting with the F.B.I.
We're taking this seriously.

1468
01:05:55,040 --> 01:05:56,960
You handle the N.T.S.B.
investigation, John.

1469
01:05:57,040 --> 01:05:58,600
We'll worry about Henry Drake.

1470
01:05:58,680 --> 01:06:01,480
- Okay.
- Alright, let's get started.

1471
01:08:00,040 --> 01:08:03,400
There's nothing unusual
about any of the entries.

1472
01:08:03,480 --> 01:08:05,800
Except for two.

1473
01:08:07,760 --> 01:08:10,280
This entry was made
three months ago, August 8th.

1474
01:08:10,360 --> 01:08:13,360
"Scope serviced, check data display,
results pass."

1475
01:08:13,440 --> 01:08:16,160
Now, everything looks normal
to the naked eye.

1476
01:08:16,240 --> 01:08:18,320
Writing's the same, ink's the same.

1477
01:08:18,400 --> 01:08:22,240
The scope I.D. number is 5321.

1478
01:08:22,320 --> 01:08:25,960
But, under infrared,
the entry looks like this.

1479
01:08:26,040 --> 01:08:30,000
Everything still looks the same
except for the scope I.D. number.

1480
01:08:30,200 --> 01:08:35,240
5321 is now 58273.

1481
01:08:35,320 --> 01:08:36,960
The three's been altered to
look like an eight...

1482
01:08:37,040 --> 01:08:40,000
the one to a seven,
and somebody's added a three.

1483
01:08:40,200 --> 01:08:41,920
5321.

1484
01:08:42,000 --> 01:08:43,240
That was Drake's scope.

1485
01:08:43,320 --> 01:08:45,160
- And the other entry?
- Same complaint...

1486
01:08:45,240 --> 01:08:47,760
same service, also passed.

1487
01:08:48,200 --> 01:08:49,400
Keep that log secure.

1488
01:08:49,480 --> 01:08:52,080
John. You're right.

1489
01:08:53,120 --> 01:08:56,320
I knew you'd find it.
Thanks, Ms. Garfield.

1490
01:09:16,440 --> 01:09:19,600
I'm not workin' traffic tomorrow
if you're thinkin' of bustin' me.

1491
01:09:20,000 --> 01:09:22,040
A draft. Want another one?

1492
01:09:22,120 --> 01:09:24,360
- I'm good, thanks.
- Just one.

1493
01:09:24,720 --> 01:09:26,360
What do you wanna talk about now?

1494
01:09:26,440 --> 01:09:28,800
Is there a question
you've not asked me?

1495
01:09:28,880 --> 01:09:30,160
Yeah.

1496
01:09:31,520 --> 01:09:34,880
Who altered the two entries
in the maintenance log book?

1497
01:09:35,200 --> 01:09:36,720
Can't help you on that one.

1498
01:09:36,800 --> 01:09:38,120
I think you can.

1499
01:09:38,200 --> 01:09:41,800
And I'm not gonna leave till you do.

1500
01:09:42,600 --> 01:09:43,800
Thanks.

1501
01:09:45,000 --> 01:09:46,680
You listen to me.

1502
01:09:46,840 --> 01:09:49,840
I've cooperated with you.
I've answered your questions.

1503
01:09:49,960 --> 01:09:51,520
You don't disrespect me
by cornin' in here...

1504
01:09:51,600 --> 01:09:54,560
and accusin' me of something
I know nothing about.

1505
01:09:55,080 --> 01:09:57,640
Were they changed before or after
the crash?

1506
01:09:57,720 --> 01:10:00,000
I don't know what the hell
you're talkin' about.

1507
01:10:00,080 --> 01:10:01,280
You guys.

1508
01:10:01,920 --> 01:10:05,680
You guys think they're just
blips on a screen, don't you?

1509
01:10:06,240 --> 01:10:08,400
You don't know what I think.

1510
01:10:08,600 --> 01:10:11,520
There is nothing you or I could
ever do to bring those people back.

1511
01:10:11,600 --> 01:10:14,800
Were they changed before or after
the crash?

1512
01:10:16,480 --> 01:10:19,560
How would I know anything
about entries in the program log?

1513
01:10:19,640 --> 01:10:21,160
'Cause you're the supervisor.

1514
01:10:21,240 --> 01:10:23,360
Only you and the lab technician
have access to it.

1515
01:10:23,440 --> 01:10:25,720
Then you should
talk to the lab technician.

1516
01:10:25,800 --> 01:10:27,360
I just did.

1517
01:10:28,520 --> 01:10:32,120
I already know you did it.
I just don't know why.

1518
01:10:36,000 --> 01:10:38,120
I got thirty years on this job.

1519
01:10:38,200 --> 01:10:41,320
I tell somebody below me
to do something, they do it.

1520
01:10:41,400 --> 01:10:44,720
Somebody above me tells me
to do something, I do it.

1521
01:10:44,840 --> 01:10:46,680
That's the way it works, man.

1522
01:10:46,840 --> 01:10:49,280
How come you don't understand that?

1523
01:10:56,280 --> 01:10:58,720
Who told you to change the log?

1524
01:11:02,280 --> 01:11:04,920
Frank Wyatt please.
It's John Dantley calling.

1525
01:11:05,520 --> 01:11:07,440
Yes, I'd. Would you please
tell him to meet me...

1526
01:11:07,520 --> 01:11:11,400
tomorrow afternoon at the crash site?
It's urgent. Thank you.

1527
01:12:06,080 --> 01:12:07,400
Okay.

1528
01:12:18,000 --> 01:12:19,280
Great.

1529
01:12:24,120 --> 01:12:25,960
The whole system's fried.

1530
01:12:26,040 --> 01:12:30,080
Repeater scope, console,
radios, everything.

1531
01:12:30,160 --> 01:12:31,720
I've never seen anything like it.

1532
01:12:31,840 --> 01:12:34,000
- Thanks, George.
- Yeah.

1533
01:12:34,200 --> 01:12:37,000
- How do you fry an entire system?
- HERF.

1534
01:12:37,080 --> 01:12:39,400
- Beg your pardon?
- High energy radio frequency.

1535
01:12:39,480 --> 01:12:41,120
They used something like it
in the Gulf War.

1536
01:12:41,200 --> 01:12:44,920
It'd shut down communications,
radar, it fries everything.

1537
01:12:53,800 --> 01:12:55,400
- Name?
- Jim Hale.

1538
01:12:55,480 --> 01:12:56,680
ID?

1539
01:13:05,520 --> 01:13:07,280
Maintenance from International?

1540
01:13:07,400 --> 01:13:08,720
Yes, sir.

1541
01:13:12,080 --> 01:13:13,520
Do you know where to park?

1542
01:13:13,600 --> 01:13:16,080
- Sure do.
- Alright, then.

1543
01:13:26,800 --> 01:13:28,480
Jim Hale from International.

1544
01:13:28,560 --> 01:13:29,960
Okay.

1545
01:13:31,240 --> 01:13:33,160
We gotcha here.
If you could just sign in for me...

1546
01:13:33,280 --> 01:13:35,120
- please.
- Yes, ma'am.

1547
01:13:36,760 --> 01:13:37,840
How's Jenny?

1548
01:13:37,920 --> 01:13:41,680
Jenny Glass? She's fine. Yeah,
she works weekends now.

1549
01:13:41,760 --> 01:13:43,440
- Well, you tell her I said hi.
- I sure will.

1550
01:13:43,520 --> 01:13:45,160
You know the code, right?

1551
01:13:45,880 --> 01:13:47,120
No actually. You know,
they had changed it...

1552
01:13:47,200 --> 01:13:48,600
after the last time
I was here, I think.

1553
01:13:48,720 --> 01:13:51,200
- Do you mind?
- Sure, no problem.

1554
01:14:00,880 --> 01:14:02,400
Thank you so much.

1555
01:14:04,760 --> 01:14:07,120
- Tell Jenny I say hi.
- I will.

1556
01:14:59,000 --> 01:15:00,680
- Meadows, I'm back.
- So, what is it...

1557
01:15:00,760 --> 01:15:02,160
you wanted me to see, John?

1558
01:15:02,240 --> 01:15:04,160
You ever been to a crash site before?

1559
01:15:04,240 --> 01:15:05,400
No.

1560
01:15:05,760 --> 01:15:07,640
Quite a smell, isn't it?

1561
01:15:08,080 --> 01:15:12,080
Each crash site
has a very unique smell.

1562
01:15:13,160 --> 01:15:18,400
Can't get rid of it. Gets on you.
Your clothes, your shoes.

1563
01:15:18,640 --> 01:15:20,440
I've never gotten used to it.

1564
01:15:20,960 --> 01:15:24,040
The 757 didn't explode on impact.

1565
01:15:24,600 --> 01:15:27,760
The tail section tore off
from the sheer force of the fall.

1566
01:15:27,840 --> 01:15:30,880
But it didn't explode.
It just spiralled down...

1567
01:15:31,000 --> 01:15:33,160
- My God.
- for two minutes.

1568
01:15:33,760 --> 01:15:38,080
Everyone was still strapped in
and alive till it hit the ground.

1569
01:15:38,320 --> 01:15:39,960
For two minutes.

1570
01:15:41,120 --> 01:15:43,400
Can you imagine what those
two minutes must've been like...

1571
01:15:43,480 --> 01:15:45,200
for those passengers?

1572
01:15:45,680 --> 01:15:46,920
No.

1573
01:15:47,720 --> 01:15:49,720
No, I can't, John.

1574
01:15:52,800 --> 01:15:56,040
See this little fan?
It's part of a scope.

1575
01:15:56,360 --> 01:15:59,800
It has one function only
to cool the unit.

1576
01:16:00,920 --> 01:16:02,920
You see, what happened the night
of the crash, a little wire...

1577
01:16:03,000 --> 01:16:05,880
connected to the fan arced.
The fan stopped working.

1578
01:16:05,960 --> 01:16:08,000
And that caused
the character generator to overheat.

1579
01:16:08,080 --> 01:16:09,320
So the scope blacked out.

1580
01:16:09,440 --> 01:16:11,920
When the scope blacked out,
the data block vanished...

1581
01:16:12,000 --> 01:16:14,440
which caused the controller to give
the wrong information to the pilot...

1582
01:16:14,520 --> 01:16:16,680
which caused the two planes
to fly into each other...

1583
01:16:16,760 --> 01:16:18,400
and kill a hundred and
eighty-five people...

1584
01:16:18,480 --> 01:16:20,800
including a woman
I knew and loved.

1585
01:16:23,600 --> 01:16:27,040
Because of this little part,
you recognize it?

1586
01:16:27,120 --> 01:16:29,000
It's from Henry Drake's scope.

1587
01:16:29,080 --> 01:16:31,560
It was replaced
the night of the crash.

1588
01:16:31,640 --> 01:16:33,520
Of course it should've been replaced
months ago when Drake said...

1589
01:16:33,600 --> 01:16:35,320
"Hey, there's something wrong
with my scope," but...

1590
01:16:35,400 --> 01:16:37,480
nobody's gonna listen to
a guy like that.

1591
01:16:37,560 --> 01:16:39,240
But after the crash...

1592
01:16:39,840 --> 01:16:43,320
somebody listened
and replaced this part.

1593
01:16:43,440 --> 01:16:45,880
And destroyed
the unsatisfactory reports he filed.

1594
01:16:46,000 --> 01:16:47,920
And nothing was said to the N.T.S.B.

1595
01:16:48,040 --> 01:16:50,080
Nothing was said when
an innocent man was blamed.

1596
01:16:50,160 --> 01:16:52,880
Nothing was said when a hundred
and eighty-five people were killed!

1597
01:16:52,960 --> 01:16:55,800
Wait a minute. Do you think that
if I knew that this would happen...

1598
01:16:55,880 --> 01:16:57,120
that I'd allow it to happen?

1599
01:16:57,200 --> 01:16:58,400
But you did allow it to happen.

1600
01:16:58,520 --> 01:17:00,200
I did not know, John.

1601
01:17:00,320 --> 01:17:01,920
- You don't understand.
- Well, tell me.

1602
01:17:02,000 --> 01:17:05,680
- Tell me what I don't understand.
- Every day, every single day...

1603
01:17:05,760 --> 01:17:10,280
I'm responsible for keeping
thousands of planes in the sky.

1604
01:17:10,360 --> 01:17:11,960
That's my job.

1605
01:17:12,040 --> 01:17:13,600
People spend longer
'n twenty minutes...

1606
01:17:13,680 --> 01:17:16,520
on the tarmac in Chicago,
John, I hear about it.

1607
01:17:17,200 --> 01:17:20,080
But I only have so much
control of airspace.

1608
01:17:20,160 --> 01:17:22,200
So many controllers, so many scopes

1609
01:17:22,280 --> 01:17:25,480
so many technicians and equipment
that breaks down.

1610
01:17:25,560 --> 01:17:27,480
I've to keep the planes
running on time...

1611
01:17:27,600 --> 01:17:30,640
with a system that
I'm just trying to keep afloat.

1612
01:17:31,800 --> 01:17:35,160
Now, I know that that's not right.

1613
01:17:36,880 --> 01:17:39,160
We make do with what we have.

1614
01:17:39,280 --> 01:17:43,600
But if it's not right,
then why do you protect it?

1615
01:17:45,760 --> 01:17:48,160
Because it's what we do.

1616
01:17:51,360 --> 01:17:52,840
Frank...

1617
01:18:06,600 --> 01:18:09,560
Yeah, Bill Kennedy, please.
It's John Dantley calling.

1618
01:18:09,640 --> 01:18:11,160
Yeah, I'll hold.

1619
01:18:28,960 --> 01:18:31,320
I don't care what time it is. Do it.

1620
01:18:31,400 --> 01:18:33,640
- Just do it.
- Right over there...

1621
01:18:33,760 --> 01:18:36,640
I want agents spread out
in a two mile radius of the facility.

1622
01:18:36,720 --> 01:18:38,320
Go!

1623
01:18:44,280 --> 01:18:45,760
- Dantley.
- Go on inside.

1624
01:18:45,840 --> 01:18:47,720
- They're expecting you.
- Thanks.

1625
01:18:57,200 --> 01:18:59,160
I say we do what he says.

1626
01:18:59,240 --> 01:19:00,480
We're running out of time, gentlemen.

1627
01:19:00,560 --> 01:19:02,200
What did the Department of
Transportation say?

1628
01:19:02,280 --> 01:19:04,840
I spoke to the Secretary
an hour ago. It's our call.

1629
01:19:04,920 --> 01:19:07,280
We shut the Midwest Center down,
that means we ground the planes...

1630
01:19:07,360 --> 01:19:08,480
the day before Thanksgiving.

1631
01:19:08,560 --> 01:19:09,960
- We're gonna ground the planes?
- Chaos.

1632
01:19:10,040 --> 01:19:11,920
We already have it.
We got two hour delays.

1633
01:19:12,000 --> 01:19:14,040
People are cancelling flights.
Phone lines are overloaded.

1634
01:19:14,120 --> 01:19:16,360
- Airports are a mess.
- Ground the planes.

1635
01:19:16,560 --> 01:19:17,880
Think of our priorities here.

1636
01:19:17,960 --> 01:19:20,760
I understand your instinct to be
cautious. It's mine, too.

1637
01:19:20,840 --> 01:19:22,280
But the threat is not
specific enough.

1638
01:19:22,360 --> 01:19:23,600
How much more specific can he be?

1639
01:19:23,680 --> 01:19:26,320
He said "ground the planes in an hour
or I'll shut this system down."

1640
01:19:26,400 --> 01:19:27,720
How?

1641
01:19:28,160 --> 01:19:30,800
He can't get inside the building.
I couldn't get inside the building.

1642
01:19:30,880 --> 01:19:32,280
He can't do it outside the building.

1643
01:19:32,360 --> 01:19:34,520
We got built-in E.M.I.
shielding that blocks frequencies.

1644
01:19:34,600 --> 01:19:36,960
What, Frank, up to ten gigahertz?

1645
01:19:37,040 --> 01:19:38,520
Radar's off-site and heavily guarded.

1646
01:19:38,600 --> 01:19:40,360
So, you'd put your wife on a plane
right now?

1647
01:19:40,440 --> 01:19:41,520
That's not the issue.

1648
01:19:41,600 --> 01:19:43,480
- That is the issue.
- Unless Henry Drake...

1649
01:19:43,560 --> 01:19:45,480
is some kind of a genius,
I cannot believe this man...

1650
01:19:45,560 --> 01:19:48,200
can shut this system down.
I cannot, in good conscience...

1651
01:19:48,280 --> 01:19:51,160
stop fifty million people from
travelling today. I can't do it.

1652
01:19:51,240 --> 01:19:54,360
He is a genius, Royer.
Ground the planes.

1653
01:19:54,440 --> 01:19:55,760
Hello?

1654
01:19:56,880 --> 01:19:59,280
John, I think you better take this.

1655
01:19:59,800 --> 01:20:01,720
- Hello?
- I'm shuttin' it down.

1656
01:20:01,800 --> 01:20:04,000
You've five minutes.

1657
01:20:04,600 --> 01:20:07,320
He's here. We've got five minutes.

1658
01:20:09,240 --> 01:20:10,600
Excuse me.

1659
01:20:11,120 --> 01:20:13,040
Watch it, coming through!

1660
01:20:14,960 --> 01:20:17,280
Check the microwave links
upstairs on the roof.

1661
01:20:17,360 --> 01:20:18,600
Got it.

1662
01:20:46,480 --> 01:20:47,720
Henry.

1663
01:20:47,880 --> 01:20:49,440
Don't come any closer.

1664
01:20:49,960 --> 01:20:51,360
Stay right there.

1665
01:20:53,320 --> 01:20:55,520
So, is anybody listening to me now?

1666
01:20:55,600 --> 01:20:57,160
Yeah, we're listening.

1667
01:20:57,560 --> 01:20:59,480
- We're all listening.
- Haven't shut it down though

1668
01:20:59,560 --> 01:21:00,880
have they?

1669
01:21:01,280 --> 01:21:04,360
- What are you doing?
- I'm gonna shut it down myself.

1670
01:21:04,440 --> 01:21:05,800
You see this?

1671
01:21:07,800 --> 01:21:10,360
I can fry this whole system.
You'd never get it back up.

1672
01:21:10,440 --> 01:21:12,760
They'd have to ground the planes
for a week.

1673
01:21:12,840 --> 01:21:15,680
And, what about the ones
up there right now?

1674
01:21:16,640 --> 01:21:18,120
